"n.逗号 【英】 n. 逗号(punctuation mark[,]to indicate a light pause) 【考】 caret : insertion / comma : pause(插字符表示插入/逗 号表示暂停)enclose : parentheses / separate : comma(括号起包括作用/逗 号起分隔作用) n. 逗号(表示句子结构内思想或要素的分开、停顿或隔开) 【记】com = come来, ma妈: 妈妈来了! 别玩了, 停顿一下! －逗号 【类】caret: insertion = comma: pause 插字符表示插入 = 逗号表示停顿enclose: parentheses = separate: comma括号起包括作用 = 逗号起分隔作用 【记】音：扣马，抠马，扣住马停下来，暂停；马上是赶快的意思；Come on，give me a break 是一句常用语与影视作品常见的台词，暂停一下，用逗号停一下； comma (n.)  1520s as a Latin word, nativized by 1590s, from Latin comma ""short phrase,"" from Greek komma ""clause in a sentence,"" literally ""piece which is cut off,"" from koptein ""to cut off,"" from PIE root *kop- ""to beat, strike"" (see hatchet (n.)). Like colon (n.1) and period, originally a Greek rhetorical term for a part of a sentence, and like them it has been transferred to the punctuation mark that identifies it."
